==Japanese==

===Etymology 1===
Derived from [[た]] by addition of [[dakuten]].

====Hiragana character====
{{ja-kana|h|rom=da}}

# The {{IPAchar|/da/}} syllable.
# The voiced form of [[た]]. The previous voiced character is [[ぞ]] and the next voiced character is [[ぢ]]. The equivalent [[katakana]] character is [[ダ]].

=====Related terms=====
* For a list of words starting with だ ('''da'''), see: [[Special:Allpages/だ]]

===Etymology 2===
Contraction of [[で]][[ある]] (''de aru'')

====Suffix====
{{ja-pos|h|particle|rom=da|hidx=た'}}

# to [[be]]

